content: While kayaking or canoeing in Hague, Virginia, you may encounter a variety of wildlife such as bald eagles, ospreys, blue herons, egrets, and other waterfowl species. You may also see river otters, muskrats, beavers, turtles, and various fish species such as striped bass, largemouth bass, bluegill, and catfish. Additionally, you may see critters such as deer, foxes, and raccoons along the shoreline while paddling. Make sure to maintain a safe distance from the wildlife and avoid disturbing their natural habitats while enjoying your paddle trip.
